<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Sleeper</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-07"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Sleeper reports that insurgents have destroyed two culverts of
                            Western Railway between towns of Pinar del Rio and San Luis and
                            interrupted traffic. He also says that emissary left for Pinar del Rio
                            on behalf of veterans to induce Pino Guerra to suspend hostilities
                            pending discussion peace negotiations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>